<%- content_for :title, "Flexible Input" -%>

<div class="content-spacing">

  <p>A flexible input is an input field that starts off small but grows when focused:</p>

  <%- content_for :example_1 do -%>
<div data-flexible-input-container>
  <div data-flexible-input="140/300">
    <input type="text" />
  </div>
</div>
  <%- end -%>
  <%= yield :example_1 -%>

  <p>The flexible input needs two elements to wrap around the input field:</p>

  <pre class="sg-pre prettyprint"><%= render_source(yield :example_1) -%></pre>

  <p>The outer wrapper needs <code>data-flexible-input-container</code> and the inner wrapper needs <code>data-flexible-input</code>. The inner wrapper takes one value in the form of <code>initial-size/focus-size</code>.

  <p>To anchor the flexible input to the right and extend to the left, simply add <code>data-flexible-input-right</code> to your <code>data-flexible-input</code> element:</p>

  <%- content_for :example_right do -%>
<div data-flexible-input-container>
  <div data-flexible-input="140/300" data-flexible-input-right>
    <input type="text" />
  </div>
</div>
  <%- end -%>
  <%= yield :example_right -%>

  <pre class="sg-pre prettyprint"><%= render_source(yield :example_right) -%></pre>

  <p>An example with <code>data-flexible-input</code> value of 200/800:</p>

  <div data-flexible-input-container>
    <div data-flexible-input="200/800">
      <input type="text" placeholder="200/800" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>An example with 20/400:</p>

  <div data-flexible-input-container>
    <div data-flexible-input="20/400">
      <input type="text" placeholder="20/400" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>An example with 300/100, getting smaller on focus:</p>

  <div data-flexible-input-container>
    <div data-flexible-input="300/100">
      <input type="text" placeholder="300/100" />
    </div>
  </div>

</div>